column5: Looking for some cat fishing spots up in the barrie area, no more than 45 min out.
That should really aggravate  the P3TA folks!
You can try the Notty. Also try Little lake in Barrie.
If you decide to take a real road trip I'll get you on some monsters someday Brian.   Art
Im afraid if I come down your way,I,ll want to stay.You got a job for me? LOL

We hammared them on the severn river last year.  You need a boat to get to the good spots.  Let me know if you plan on going up there, I can point you in the right direction.  We managed about a dozen last time we went up.  We where trying for pickerel, not even targetting them!
Your a hard workin gent. we can always find you a job no problem.   Art
I can find him a green card.
Find slow/deep holes on the notty and fish from shore. I caught lots of tasty yellow cats from there. Heavy sinker and a worm
where abouts in the notty? south or north of angus?
Still waiting for the phone to ring Brian.   Spiel might be game for it too.   Art
Around the Flos road 4 I believe. North of Angus.
Yes. Lots of good slow and deep water there.
